{"questionId":"23220","questionHtml":"<p>The molar mass of an ideal gas is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math>. A fixed mass <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> of the gas expands at a constant pressure <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>. The graph shows the variation with temperature <em>T</em> of the gas volume <em>V</em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/4c171c36fdd37e0b1e3f4753c1309a72ca42fbb8.png\"></p>\n<p>What is the gradient of the graph?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>M</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"23220","referenceCode":"21N.1.HL.TZ0.10","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The molar mass of an ideal gas is M. A fixed mass m of the gas expands at a constant pressure p. The graph shows the variation with temperature T of the gas volume V. What is the g","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"10","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics","3.2 – Modelling a gas","Core","Topic 3: Thermal physics"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}